==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Yester
<hw>Yes"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Yesterday</er>.]</ety> <def>Last; last past; next before; of or
pertaining to yesterday.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[An enemy] whom <qex>yester</qex> sun beheld⟦br⟧
Mustering her charms.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This word is now seldom used except in a few compounds;
as, <xex>yester</xex>day, <xex>yester</xex>night, etc.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yesterday</ent>⟦br⟧
